to part friends.

00:56.804 --> 00:58.605
Maybe, we can wait
until the end of summer.

00:58.639 --> 00:59.806
Yes!

01:04.778 --> 01:06.713
You have a nice walk?
Yeah, it's nice out today.

01:06.747 --> 01:08.548
I think I may take Robie
and go down to the pool.

01:08.582 --> 01:09.682
What, you're not going
to take him to daycare?

01:09.717 --> 01:11.451
I am daycare.

01:12.620 --> 01:13.820
You know we can't
keep on doing this.

01:13.854 --> 01:16.422
What's wrong?
Ready for me to go home?

01:16.457 --> 01:18.791
No. Not really.

01:18.826 --> 01:20.827
I just think it's kind of

01:20.861 --> 01:23.630
unusual for us to be enjoying
life this much. That's all.

01:23.664 --> 01:26.633
Yeah, it is. I don't really
remember when we were this happy.

01:26.667 --> 01:30.403
When the girls were babies,
we were this happy, I think.

01:30.437 --> 01:32.605
Yeah. I like babies.

01:32.640 --> 01:34.540
They can't talk,
they don't have opinions,

01:34.575 --> 01:37.777
