something, the way they look at you.

01:37.811 --> 01:39.646
Remember when Ashley and Amy
used to look at us like that?

01:39.680 --> 01:42.682
Yeah, I do.
But...

01:42.716 --> 01:44.584
But Robie's going to
grow up and find out

01:44.618 --> 01:45.652
we don't know
what we're doing either

01:45.686 --> 01:47.654
and then poof!
The magic is gone.

01:47.688 --> 01:49.622
Luckily, he's a little more
easygoing than the girls.

01:49.657 --> 01:50.823
He takes after me in that
regard, don't you think?

01:50.858 --> 01:52.692
I think that's
a recessive gene,

01:52.726 --> 01:54.694
so I don't think
it's either one of us.

01:54.728 --> 01:56.663
You're probably right.
But I have mellowed a lot, haven't I?

01:56.697 --> 01:57.830
Well, we'll see
when Ashley calls.

01:57.865 --> 02:00.600
She better call.
Unless she's too busy working.

02:00.634 --> 02:01.734
